description: Gets a list of the associations between queues and limits defined in a farm.

parameters.name: farmId
parameters.description: The unique identifier of the farm that contains the limits and associations.

nested_items.name: queueLimitAssociations
nested_items.description: A list of associations between limits and queues in the farm specified in the request.

nested_items.name: createdAt
nested_items.description: The Unix timestamp of the date and time that the association was created.

nested_items.name: createdBy
nested_items.description: The user identifier of the person that created the association.

nested_items.name: updatedAt
nested_items.description: The Unix timestamp of the date and time that the association was last updated.

nested_items.name: updatedBy
nested_items.description: The user identifier of the person that updated the association.

nested_items.name: queueId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the queue in the association.

nested_items.name: limitId
nested_items.description: The unique identifier of the limit in the association.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of task scheduling in the queue-limit association.
STOP_LIMIT_USAGE_AND_COMPLETE_TASKS - Association has stopped scheduling new tasks and is completing current tasks.
STOP_LIMIT_USAGE_AND_CANCEL_TASKS - Association has stopped scheduling new tasks and is canceling current tasks.

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: If Deadline Cloud returns nextToken, then there are more results available. The value of nextToken is a unique pagination token for each page. To retrieve the next page, call the operation again using the returned token. Keep all other arguments unchanged. If no results remain, then nextToken is set to null. Each pagination token expires after 24 hours. If you provide a token that isn't valid, then you receive an HTTP 400 ValidationException error.
